The paper discusses the parallelization of algorithms for solving polynomial systems symbolically, which involves both low-level arithmetic operations and high-level procedures for producing different components of the solution set. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to symbolic computation, numerical analysis, and parallel computing. Specifically, cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are all possible sub-categories that could be relevant to this paper.
